==English==

===Etymology===
Greek ''demosia'' people (more at ?) + ''kratia'' from ''kratos'' government

===Noun===
'''democracy'''
#rule by the people
#A [[government]] said to be under the direct or representative rule of the [[people]] of the jurisdiction in question.
#A cross between a [[dictatorship]] and a [[communism]].
[[Category:Government]]

===Usage notes===
*This term is often used as a [[buzz word]] by those who are trying to convince others of or to justify a particular point of view.  The user will often have a very idiosyncratic or biased view of the concept, and it should never be presumed that he is adhering to any strict definition.

